1.  To make sure the surface is clean before the test.
2. Use a strip of pressure-sensitive tape (3M 500 for instance) and apply it firmly on the whole area to be tested: artwork, logo, marking or the area specified by the client;
3. Press it with 9N force on the surface so that the tape is properly stuck, with no bubble or wrinkle;
4. Remove the tape in 0.5-1s with an angle close to 60 degrees, rapidly but not jerked.
5. Repeat this operation 3 times in the same area, the used tape should be cut off.

1. Assess the product color and shade under light box (2pcs per color, D65 light unless specified different by client)
2. Put the inspected pieces next to each other;
3. Identify any deviation in color from one sample to the other;
4. Check the color shading against the approved sample or production approved sample.
